    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I want to echo the comment here made by @jtattermusch on #14875: \"is there a way to setup automated testing for this? If not, it is likely that the build will get broken soon. Note that our test farm doesn't provide any solaris machines to test with.\" We take our testing responsibility seriously for platforms that we support, and we're pretty firm in the opinion that a non-tested platform (or piece of code) is a non-working platform (or piece of code). I don't have a realistic opinion of how to move forward on this category of issues, but perhaps there's some way where the folks looking for Solaris/AIX/etc support can make this possible? Perhaps by keeping a regularly-patched and tested version in their own repo?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"
  },
