    "created_at": "2018-08-19T10:05:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-08-19T10:05:02Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@vjpai Let me first say thanks for your time and I realize this is not your problem.\r\n\r\nI would have no trouble in maintaining a separate repo however (my) problem with that is that a lot of Bazel projects include gRPC (including, ironically, Bazel itself) which automatically means those projects can't be build without patching on SmartOS / Illumos / Solaris. \r\n\r\nWhat would be an acceptable automated test environment for you guys? Vagrant image? Cloud VM? KVM? I did some digging but I can find the tests but I can't seem to find how the automated tests for the various platforms (FreeBSD, macOS, etc.) are actually launched / managed. Could you point me in the right direction for those? I could then probably create an Illumos based test environment."
  },
